r mission will be to research, analyse and classify existing and future smart contracts and smart contract technologies with the purpose of protecting and advising CipherTrace\u2019s customers on existing and planned smart contract deployments. To be successful, you should have experience in the following areas: BS in Computer Science or Math or equivalent experience 2+ years of experience as a Software Developer 5+ years of experience as an Application Security Auditor Deep understanding of OWASP Top security threats and how they apply to smart contracts and crypto currencies in general Hands-on experience building smart contracts and thorough understand of the Ethereum implementation (including its ABI and EVM). Experience with reverse engineering technologies and techniques Nice to have: MS in Computer Science, Statistics or Data Analytics. Understanding and hands-on experience at the blockchain/daemon/protocol level with any smart contract enabled crypto currency. Very familiar with the Ethereum protocol layer, advancements with upcoming EIPs and Eth 2.0. Familiar with security implications of the Solidity langauge, EVM bytecode, and common smart contract exploits. Experience integrating cryptocurrencies with other services and building the tools required to extract information from the blockchains. Familiarity with AWS (EC2, VPC, Security Groups, ECS, RDS (Aurora and MySQL), SNS, CloudWatch, CloudTrail, Lambda functions, Parameter Store, Cloud Formation, S3, Glacier, IAM. Perks & Benefits We offer a comprehensive benefits package including competitive salaries, stock options for senior roles, medical, dental and vision \u2013 which cover domestic partners as well \u2013 plus life and disability coverage, 20 vacation days, and a 401K plan. If you are interested, send your resume to [email protected] ", 
